From: art-suite conda packaging
Subject: [PATCH] Add missing <cassert> includes for assert()

Many art TUs call assert() without including <cassert> (e.g.
art/Framework/IO/Sources/detail/FileServiceProxy.cc: "'assert' was not declared
in this scope"). Older libstdc++ leaked the macro in transitively; conda-forge's
newer libstdc++ does not. Add the missing direct includes. Same class of fix as
fhiclcpp #4 (DatabaseSupport.cc). Only non-test TUs are touched (BUILD_TESTING=OFF).
Generated against the tree with 0001/0002 already applied. See potential_improvements.md.

